<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="573" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d573">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.61/289a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="to">Grew</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-20T18:00:00-05:00">October 20, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>99. For your information, the President made public this afternoon an
                                exchange of messages between himself and the President of the All
                                Union Executive Committee, Moscow, in consequence of which it is to
                                be expected that the Russian Government will send to Washington <pb facs="0900" n="796" xml:id="pg_796"/> Litvinoff, Commissar for
                                Foreign Affairs, to discuss questions outstanding between the two
                                countries. In commenting briefly to press correspondents upon this
                                action, the President explained that this step does not constitute
                                recognition.</p>
                            <p>Text is being sent by naval radio to Peiping for relay to you.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>